<task id="010" project="ai-spaarke-action-engine-r1">
  <metadata>
    <title>Dataverse Schema — Action Entities (sprk_action, sprk_actiontemplate, sprk_actioninstance, sprk_actionrun)</title>
    <phase>Phase 1: Foundation</phase>
    <status>not-started</status>
    <estimated-hours>5</estimated-hours>
    <dependencies>001</dependencies>
    <blocks>020, 021, 022, 040, 041, 042, 050, 053, 054, 055</blocks>
    <tags>dataverse, solution, fields</tags>
    <rigor-hint>FULL</rigor-hint>
    <rigor-reason>Creates four foundational Dataverse entities whose schema is consumed by all Phase 2+ tasks; mis-shaped fields force expensive rework downstream; has explicit constraint set (ADR-002, ADR-017) and depends on task 001</rigor-reason>
    <parallel-group>A</parallel-group>
    <parallel-safe>true</parallel-safe>
    <parallel-reason>Touches only sprk_action / sprk_actiontemplate / sprk_actioninstance / sprk_actionrun entity definitions; disjoint from tasks 011 (sprk_toolregistry), 012 (sprk_gate_approval), 013 (sprk_aichatcontextmap extension)</parallel-reason>
  </metadata>

  <prompt>
    Create the four canonical Action Engine Dataverse entities — `sprk_action`, `sprk_actiontemplate`, `sprk_actioninstance`, `sprk_actionrun` — with the fields specified in spec.md FR-01..FR-06 and design §5. Use the `dataverse-create-schema` skill (Web API + Python SDK pattern) since PAC CLI does not support table/column creation. Status field on `sprk_actionrun` MUST use the ADR-017 canonical state sequence `Queued | Running | Completed | Failed | Poisoned | Cancelled`.
  </prompt>

  <role>
    SPAARKE Dataverse schema engineer with hands-on experience using the `dataverse-create-schema` skill (Web API EntityDefinitions + Python SDK) to author publisher-prefixed entities, relationships, and option-sets that survive ALM packaging and round-trip without drift.
  </role>

  <goal>
    Four Dataverse tables created in the dev environment under publisher prefix `sprk_`, each with the field set required by spec.md FR-01..FR-06 and design §5:
    1. **`sprk_action`** — Action Definition: identity, owner (User lookup), template ref (lookup → `sprk_actiontemplate`), playbookId (lookup → `sprk_aiplaybook`), parameterValues (JSON), triggerSpec (Choice + JSON payload), authRequirements (JSON), humanGateConfig (JSON), outputContract (JSON), governance (JSON: feature flag + kill switch per ADR-018), tenantId (text).
    2. **`sprk_actiontemplate`** — Template: identity, parameterSchema (JSON Schema text), defaults (JSON), validationRules (JSON), naturalLanguageDescription (text), discoverabilityMetadata (JSON), classification (Choice: Deterministic / AI / Hybrid).
    3. **`sprk_actioninstance`** — Instance: identity, template ref (lookup → `sprk_actiontemplate`), parameterBlob (JSON), tenantId (text).
    4. **`sprk_actionrun`** — Run record: identity, action ref (lookup → `sprk_action`), instance ref (lookup → `sprk_actioninstance`), **status (Choice: Queued, Running, Completed, Failed, Poisoned, Cancelled — exact ADR-017 sequence)**, inputs (JSON), stepOutcomes (JSON), correlationId (text), attemptCount (integer), approvalHistory (JSON), tenantId (text), startedAt (DateTime), completedAt (DateTime, nullable).

    All four entities packed into the Action Engine solution (`SpaarkeActionEngine` or per-existing-solution choice in plan.md). Deliverable: solution import succeeds in dev environment, all four entities visible in the maker portal, lookups resolve correctly.
  </goal>

  <context>
    <background>
      The Action sits **above** the existing JPS Playbook entity (`sprk_aiplaybook`) per coordination assessment §4.1 — Action.playbookId is a FK to Playbook (FR-05). Deletion of a referenced Playbook MUST be blocked (referential integrity).

      Run status states are ADR-017 canonical: `Queued | Running | Completed | Failed | Poisoned | Cancelled`. Do NOT invent new states. The `Poisoned` state matches `ServiceBusJobProcessor` poison-message semantics (ADR-004).

      `sprk_action` carries the trigger spec discriminator (Manual | Scheduled) — Manual has `null` payload; Scheduled has a cron expression. The scheduler chosen in task 001 will consume this field.

      Tenant scoping: every entity carries `tenantId` (text). All queries from BFF filter by tenantId per NFR-05. Multi-tenant isolation is mechanical via field, not implicit.

      Triggers via Dataverse webhooks are R2 scope (per plan.md ADR-002 note). MVP triggers are manual + cron-via-scheduler. Do NOT implement Dataverse plugins on these entities.

      The `dataverse-create-schema` skill is the canonical approach since PAC CLI lacks `pac table create` / `pac column create`. Use Web API EntityDefinitions for table creation and Python SDK (`dataverse-sdk`) for bulk field creation.
    </background>
    <relevant-files>
      <file>projects/ai-spaarke-action-engine-r1/spec.md</file>
