  <steps>
    <step order="0">Context check: confirm working tree clean, branch is `work/ai-spaarke-action-engine-r1`, baseline build passes, task 001 status is ✅ in TASK-INDEX.md. Load the `dataverse-create-schema` skill. (task-execute Step 0)</step>
    <step order="1">Read spec.md FR-01..FR-06, design §5, and coordination-assessment-with-insights-engine.md §4.1. Confirm field shapes against spec — esp. status states (ADR-017) and trigger spec discriminator.</step>
    <step order="2">Determine solution targeting: either an existing Action Engine solution or create a new `SpaarkeActionEngine` unmanaged solution under publisher prefix `sprk_`. Document decision in `notes/decisions/solution-targeting.md`.</step>
    <step order="3">Author the four entity schemas as Python / Web API scripts. Start with `sprk_actiontemplate` (no lookups), then `sprk_actioninstance` (FK to template), then `sprk_action` (FK to template + FK to existing `sprk_aiplaybook`), then `sprk_actionrun` (FK to action + FK to instance). Lookups: `sprk_action.playbookId` uses Referential Restrict behavior; other lookups use Referential.</step>
    <step order="4">Apply field-set per &lt;goal&gt; section. JSON fields use Text(Memo) with `Format = TextArea`. Choice columns: `sprk_actionrun.status` uses the canonical 6-state Choice; `sprk_actiontemplate.classification` uses the 3-value Choice (Deterministic / AI / Hybrid); `sprk_action.triggerSpec` discriminator uses the 2-value Choice (Manual / Scheduled) plus a separate Text(Memo) field `triggerSpecPayload` for the cron string or null.</step>
    <step order="5">Run the schema scripts against the dev environment. Confirm via Web API GET on each EntityDefinition that all fields landed.</step>
    <step order="6">Pack the solution and export to `src/dataverse/solutions/SpaarkeActionEngine/` (or chosen target). Verify the export contains all four entities and all fields.</step>
    <step order="7">Smoke-test in maker portal: create one record per entity, verify lookups resolve, verify Choice values render with expected labels, verify `tenantId` is mandatory.</step>
    <step order="8">Document the schema in `docs/data-model/action-engine-entities.md` (entity-by-entity field list + ERD). This becomes the source of truth that Phase 2+ tasks reference for typing.</step>
    <step order="9">Run quality gates per task-execute Step 9.5: `code-review` on the schema scripts + the schema doc; `adr-check` confirms ADR-002 (no plugins added) and ADR-017 (status states canonical).</step>
    <step order="9.5">Re-run the relevant tests: `dotnet build src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/` confirms no regression. (No new C# code in this task, but verifies the solution import didn't break downstream metadata generation if any T4/source generators consume entity metadata.)</step>
    <step order="10">Update `tasks/TASK-INDEX.md`: mark task 010 ✅; verify it unblocks tasks 020, 021, 022, 040, 041, 042, 050, 053, 054, 055. Reset `current-task.md` to point to next pending task in Group A or B.</step>
    <step order="11">Document any deviations from this plan in `projects/ai-spaarke-action-engine-r1/notes/handoffs/task-010-handoff.md` and add a brief commit message recap.</step>
  </steps>

